comment:
* This class represents a set of exceptions that can occur when requesting a
 * {@link CallEndpoint} change.

variables.name: ERROR_ENDPOINT_DOES_NOT_EXIST
variables.comment: * The operation has failed because requested CallEndpoint does not exist.

variables.name: ERROR_REQUEST_TIME_OUT
variables.comment: * The operation was not completed on time.

variables.name: ERROR_ANOTHER_REQUEST
variables.comment: * The operation was canceled by another request.

variables.name: ERROR_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: * The operation has failed due to an unknown or unspecified error.

variables.name: CREATOR
variables.comment: * Responsible for creating CallEndpointException objects for deserialized Parcels.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
private static String getMessage(String message, int code)
